    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-06-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/4937</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Group</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-06-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 22, 1926</hi>
                        </date>.<lb/>[Received June 23.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hukuang Railways Loan</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to our letter of June 15th<note n="28"
                        xml:id="d732fn28">Not printed.</note> transmitting texts of various cables
                    relating to the receipt of funds from China to apply on the service of this
                    loan, we hand you herewith for the information of the Department copy of a
                    further cablegram (No. 4759) received by us on June 18th from London.<note
                        n="28" xml:id="d732fn27">Not printed.</note> In accordance therewith we have
                    announced that beginning Thursday, June 24th, we will pay coupons from bonds of
                    the German issue of this loan which matured June 15, 1920 and June 15, 1925. We
                    also enclose copy of a letter dated June 2nd from Messrs. Morgan Grenfell &amp;
                    Co., London, transmitting to us text of a legal opinion obtained by the Hongkong
                    &amp; Shanghai Banking Corporation regarding the liability of the Chinese
                    Government to pay interest on drawn bonds until such bonds are finally
                        redeemed.<note n="28" xml:id="d732fn26">Not printed.</note> We deem this
                    opinion of considerable importance.</p>
                <p>Respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">J. P. Morgan</hi> &amp; Co.,<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">For the American Group</hi>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
